# .gcloudignore — controls what `gcloud builds submit` / `gcloud run deploy --source`
# uploads as the Cloud Build source context.
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS:
# When absent, gcloud falls back to .gitignore. Our .gitignore has a blanket
# `*.png` rule (for screenshots/figures), which silently excludes the dashboard's
# committed platform icons (services/dashboard/public/icons/*.png) from the upload
# tarball. The resulting Cloud Run image ships without those PNGs, so every PNG
# icon 404s in production while SVGs render fine. Local `docker build` uses
# .dockerignore (no *.png rule), so the breakage does not reproduce locally.
#
# This file inherits .gitignore's excludes, then rescues the committed binary
# assets the app needs baked into the image.

# gcloud's implicit excludes (only automatic when NO .gcloudignore exists — once
# this file is present we must restate them, or the whole .git/ tree gets uploaded).
.git
.gitignore
.gcloudignore

#!include:.gitignore

# Rescue committed PNG assets that .gitignore's blanket `*.png` would exclude.
!services/dashboard/public/**/*.png
!**/public/**/*.png
